summary: This is a travel voucher approval notification for a trip related to the Epstein investigation. It documents expenses for a witness interview conducted in Beverly Hills, CA from February 25-29, 2020, with a total cost of $1,981.97.

events.title: Epstein Investigation Witness Interview Trip
events.description: A trip was conducted for the purpose of interviewing a witness in the Epstein investigation in Beverly Hills, CA.

events.title: Travel Voucher Approval
events.description: Final travel voucher 11063602-1(1) for the Epstein investigation witness interview trip was approved.

keyFacts: A travel voucher was approved on March 24, 2020, for expenses related to the Epstein investigation.
The trip's purpose was a witness interview in Beverly Hills, CA, occurring from February 25 to 29, 2020.
The total expenses for the trip were $1,981.97 against an estimated cost of $2,004.11.
The document is an internal DOJ notification regarding the reimbursement process for investigation-related travel.
The voucher references a specific investigation code: R20NYS13404 - Epstein Investigation.
